    <article>
      <h1 id="article-title">What is element bending?</h1>
      <p id="first-article">
        There are four major elements: air, water, earth, and fire. Each is unique
        yet they are all connected. Throughout this site you will be introduced
        to each one. Please note, this is only an introduction. You will need to
        find a master on your own.
      </p>
      <figure class="main-image">
        <img src="https://static0.cbrimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Avatar-The-Last-Airbender-Aang-Avatar-State.jpg?q=50&fit=crop&w=960&h=500&dpr=1.5">
          <figcaption> Avatar Aang: The Last Airbender.
          </figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="small-container">
      <p id="second-article">
      </p>
      <h2 id="second-article-title">Mastering your element.</h2>
      <p> Not everyone is born with the capability to bend an element. There are
      many warriors and fighters that are highly skilled and can defeat an element
      bender. Please be sure to continue your training and master your element.
      For some it will be quick to learn, for others it might take up to years.
      </p>
      <h3 id="third-article-title">The Avatar</h3>
      <figure class="section-image">
        <img src="https://www.indiewire.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/korra-backlash.png">
        <figcaption> Avatar Korra.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
      <p id="third-article">
        If you thought mastering one element was hard, the Avatar must master
        all four elements. They are the only being able to bend all four elements.
        The Avatar is reincarnated after the next. Avatar Aang was the last airbender
        during his time. Following his legacy was Avatar Korra. Both Avatars had
        learned and mastered all four elements, just as the Avatars before them
        have.
      </p>
